DELETE FROM orders
DELETE FROM orders;
[DAY 24] NESTED vs REQUIRES_NEW:

  NESTED:
    - Same connection, same TX, uses JDBC savepoint.
    - Inner failure → rolls back to savepoint (outer TX unaffected).
    - Outer failure → ALL data lost (nested included).
    - Use for: partial batch recovery.

  REQUIRES_NEW:
    - New connection, new independent TX.
    - Outer failure → inner already committed. Survives.
    - More resource-intensive (2 connections at same time).
    - Use for: audit log, payment records that must survive.

  NESTED with JPA (Spring 6 NOTE):
    - JpaTransactionManager does NOT support NESTED.
    - Use DataSourceTransactionManager + JdbcTemplate for NESTED.
]]></system-out>
